comments.body:
Thank you @eulores for mentioning ServiceName in https://github.com/containers/podman/issues/27015.

The solution I proposed could be implemented using ServiceName=test-volume@ in test@.volume. It seems to be working. No more workarounds necessary.

@Luap99, I'm not sure if this bug should stay open. While the solution now exists, I'm not sure it was meant for this issue, and the default behaviour is still problematic.

@Luap99 

https://github.com/containers/podman/issues/25902 is exactly the same issue as this issue, and the workaround with ServiceName from two messages above will help them fully resolve the problem the right way (even though the workaround should just be default behaviour of podman and not necessary as a separate intervention).

https://github.com/containers/podman/issues/23215 is an issue that stems from the same underlying principle of naming, but for networks, not volumes, yes.
